25|$|On July 31, 1906, the American Archbishop of Manila Jeremiah James Harty {{assisted}} the religious sisters in the canonical erection of Mother Ignacia's congregation, which was previously postponed in {{the filing of}} 1732 due to an incorrect process of petitioning to Rome. On March 17, 1907, Pope Pius X promulgated the Decretum Laudis (English: Decree of Praise) in favour of the congregation's Rules and Constitutions. The Decree of <b>Approbation</b> was granted by Pope Pius XI on March 24, 1931, which made it a Congregation of Pontifical right. On January 12, 1948 (the 200th anniversary {{of the death of}} Mother Ignacia del Espíritu Santo), Pope Pius XII issued the Decree of Definitive Papal <b>Approbation</b> of the Constitutions.|$|E
