5000|$|This {{book was}} {{formerly}} published as Talmudic Terminology, having been plagiarized from Moses Mielziner's Introduction to the Talmud (1894) as was noted in brief by Rabbi Dr. Marc B. Shapiro. Shortly after publication, {{the book was}} reprinted (1988) with its title page identifying it as an adaptation from M. Mielziner, along with some small changes, and concurrently, the <b>approbations</b> by Rabbis Ovadia Yosef and Aharon Feldman were removed. In the second edition (revised and expanded, 1996) however, the <b>approbations</b> were reinstated and other changes were made including mention of Mielziner on the inside title page (similar to the reprinted first edition) but {{no longer on the}} book's front cover; on the back cover, explicit mention of the book being [...] "an adaptation of one section in Mielziner's book" [...] (i.e., part III); and the omission of chapter 12.|$|R
