25|$|There are two signings, {{sometimes}} also referenced as two <b>approbations.</b> The {{difference is}} that four signatories of the first part testify that they have examined the treatises and endorse its text while in the second signing signatories do not assert that they have read the treatises but nonetheless express approval by explicitly restating some general propositions of the treatises and endorsing them instead.|$|R
